04118nam a22006255i 9780823292257DE-B159720220524034747.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220524t20222012nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232922577 a10.1515/97808232922572doi  a(DE-B1597)566100  a(OCoLC)1306539667  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aREL0490002bisacsh1 aBartholomew, Ecumenical Patriarch, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aOn Earth as in Heaven :bEcological Vision and Initiatives of Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew /cEcumenical Patriarch Bartholomew; ed. by John Chryssavgis. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2022] 4c©2012  a1 online resource (388 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aOrthodox Christianity and Contemporary Thought0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOver the past two decades, the world has witnessed alarming environmental degradation—climate change, the loss of biodiversity, and the pollution of natural resources—together with a failure to implement environmental policies and an ever-widening gap between rich and poor. As this new volume of his writings reveals, Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew has continually proclaimed the primacy of spiritual values in determining environmental ethics and action. For him, the predicament we face is not primarily ecological but in fact spiritual: The ultimate aim is to see all things in God, and God in all things. On Earth as in Heaven demonstrates just why His All Holiness has been dubbed the “Green Patriarch” by former Vice President Al Gore (recipient of the Nobel Peace Prize for his environmental activism) and the media. This third and final volume of the spiritual leader’s selected writings showcases his statements on environmental degradation, global warming, and climate change. It contains numerous speeches and interviews in various circumstances, including ecological symposia, academic seminars, and regional and international events, over the first twenty years of his ministry. This volume also encompasses a selection of pastoral letters and exhortations—ecclesiastical, ecumenical, and academic—by His All Holiness for occasions such as Easter and Christmas, honorary doctorates, and academic awards. On Earth as in Heaven is a rich collection, essential for religious scholars, those looking for a deeper understanding of Orthodox Christianity, and anyone concerned with the environmental and social issues we face today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Orthodox.2bisacsh1 aChryssavgis, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329225740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823292257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823292257/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK